source(25.10)                                                    source(25.10)

Name
       source

Syntax
       source

        [-help]

        filename

       [-quiet  | -verbose ] [-quiet  | -echo ]

       Reads  a  file and executes the commands in the file (scripts). You can
       source an encrypted file created by the encrypt command. To be sourced,
       the file must have suffix "p" added to  the  file  name,  for  example,
       test.tcl being encrypted as test.tclp.

       Parameters

       -help  Describes the command usage.

       <filename>
              Specifies the name of the file to source.

              Data_type: string, required

       -quiet Disable verbose source.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -verbose
              Enable verbose source.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -echo  Enable verbose source.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       With  no -quiet, -verbose, -echo argument, file is sourced according to
       the
           enc_source_verbose
          global.

       Note that the setting of -quiet, -verbose, -echo argument only  affects
       the  verbosity  of  sourcing  the outermost file. If that file contains
       nested source commands, the verbosity of those nested commands is  con-
       trolled  by  their  associated [-quiet | -verbose | -echo] arguments or
       the
           enc_source_verbose
          global if no arguments.

Related Information
              * enc_source_verbose

              * enc_source_continue_on_error

              * enc_source_echo_filename

